<dl id="n12118b"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12118b">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12118b"> 118(b)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Scotus v Thomas</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[suggested by context]</font> <small> <a name="STCM" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#STCM"><cite title="source">Saint Colomban</cite></a> (1905) 192</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: See also: <a name="n12048b" href="n12all.htm#n12048b">N12 (VI.B.14):048(b)</a>. A great part of the article &lsquo;Duns Scotus&rsquo;, in the <cite>Catholic Encyclopedia</cite> is devoted to an analysis of the difference in the systems of the two great scholastics. Scotus is associated with the Franciscans while St. Thomas Aquinas is associated with the Dominicans. </mm> </dd></dl>
